f=Cybersecurity/warden/custom/security-exception-process/SKILL.md · in=disciplined way say "yes, temporarily" something violates security policy without exception becoming permanent forgotten. exception time-boxed, carries compensating control, names risk-owner, expires (fail-closed) discipline edge scout apply their gates, applied security waivers. · p=Real businesses need exceptions legacy system can't MFA yet, vendor without DPA during pilot. danger isn't exception; it's *permanent, forgotten* exception quietly becomes breach. process makes exceptions safe: bounded, mitigated, owned, self-expiring. · wu=Something needs violate security policy temporarily., "Can get exception X," "waiver," "we can't meet control yet.", Exception review/expiry cadence. · st:/ Protocol=REQUEST (what policy/control excepted, why, long) COMPENSATING CONTROL (what reduces risk meanwhile partial mitigation required; "just ignore control" denied) RISK OWNER (the residual risk warden's risk-register; named owner accountable) APPROVE (time-boxed; high-risk exceptions route board like any risk acceptance) EXPIRY hard expiry date; expiry exception closed explicitly renewed never silently extended; **fail-closed** expired exception reverts policy) TRACK (append-only register; count open exceptions itself risk signal). · in=**No exception without compensating control.** "We can't MFA legacy box" "so it's network-isolated monitored meanwhile." exception zero mitigation unmanaged risk; denied. **Time-boxed, always.** exception expiry; permanent exception. expiry it's closed (policy re-applies) explicitly renewed fresh justification silent extension forbidden (edge/scout's fail-closed). **Residual risk register, owner named.** risk remains after compensating control risk-register entry owner; high residual risk routes board (it's risk-acceptance decision). **Expiry fails closed.** exception lapses, system reverts secure policy default "well, fine before." expired-exception state loud one. **Open-exception count signal.** growing pile exceptions means policy doesn't fit reality (revise it) discipline slipping surfaced warden operator, absorbed. **warden processes; doesn't self-approve high risk.** Low-risk exceptions warden approve policy; high-risk ones operator's/board's call (the security-inversion warden recommends, operator decides). · of=`## Exception: [id] — policy/control: [what's excepted] \· Reason \· Duration → EXPIRY [date, hard] \· Compensating control: [required] \· Residual risk → register [R-ref] \· Owner \· Approval: [warden(low) / board(high)] \· State: open / expired→policy-reverted / renewed-[date]` · pr=**No compensating control, exception** bare waiver denied., **Time-boxed, always** permanent exceptions; renewal explicit., **Expiry fails closed** lapse reverts secure default., **Residual risk owned registered** high risk board., **Exception count risk signal** pile means policy's wrong., **warden recommends; operator/board accept high risk** inversion. · f=Emergency needs immediate exception grant shortest safe window strongest available compensating control, log it, schedule proper review never open-ended emergency waiver., Exception can't mitigated it's exception, it's accepted risk straight risk-register operator/board decision. · b:with Other Skills=**risk-register** (sibling): exception's residual risk lives there; high-risk board., **security-policy-framework** (sibling): exceptions waivers *of* controls; pile exceptions one control means revise policy., **board (Governance)**: high-risk exception approval risk acceptance, gated there., **keyring bastion cortex veil**: exceptions their controls (an un-MFA'd account, unhardened box) processed their compensating controls.